    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1579"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1579">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.62/52.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">German Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 17, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: I enclose, for your
                    information, a paraphrase of a telegram dated April 15, 1 p.m. from the American
                    Consul at Chihuahua, regarding the procedure in the matter of making
                    representations to the Constitutionalists in the case of the German subject
                    Radke.</p>
                <p>In this connection, I beg to invite your attention to a note the Department is
                    to-day addressing you on the subject of representations to General Venustiano
                    Carranza in behalf of the nationals of all foreign governments.<note n="152"
                        xml:id="d1579fn152">See Protection of Spanish Interests, <ref
                            target="#pg_807">p. 807</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
